KEY ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS
==========================
- GUI talks to PowerShell via persistent pwsh child process (stdin/stdout with marker-based response delimiting)
- All PS functions support -AsJson flag; the bridge auto-appends it
- IPC: main.ts registers 3 handlers: ps:invoke, ps:check-pwsh, ps:get-status
- Renderer is fully isolated (contextIsolation: true, nodeIntegration: false)
- Preload exposes window.stablelabel = { invoke, checkPwsh, getStatus }
- Routing: simple useState-based page switching in App.tsx (not react-router, despite it being a dependency in package.json)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS with dark theme throughout
- Command timeout: 300 seconds (powershell-bridge.ts:148)


WHAT'S COMPLETE (no work needed)
=================================
PowerShell Module:
  - All 87 functions implemented (no TODO/FIXME/NotImplemented markers found)
  - -AsJson standardized across all functions
  - Dry-run support on all mutation operations
  - Connection management with session age tracking

GUI Pages — All 10 pages built with full CRUD where applicable:
  - Dashboard: stats cards + recent audit log + navigation shortcuts
  - Labels: tabbed (Labels, Policies, Auto-Label) with list/detail/form for each
  - Retention: tabbed (Labels, Policies) with list/detail/form for each
  - DLP: tabbed (Policies, Rules, Sensitive Info Types) with list/detail/form
  - Documents: 4-tab layout (Lookup, Apply, Remove, Bulk)
  - Protection: 5-tab layout (Config, Templates, Onboarding, Tracking, Logs) — all panels functional
  - Elevation: 5 panels (SuperUser, SiteAdmin, Mailbox, PIM, Jobs + Status) — ALL fully wired to PS functions
  - Snapshots: list/detail/create/diff — full snapshot lifecycle
  - Analysis: 7 sections all wired to PS functions (Readiness, Permissions, Health, Conflicts, Alignment, Mismatches, Report)
  - Templates: 4 hardcoded compliance templates (PHI/PCI/PII/GDPR) with deploy + dry-run

Build & Dev:
  - Electron Forge configured for Win/Mac/Linux
  - Vite for dev + build (main, preload, renderer configs)
  - PowerShell module bundled via extraResource in packagerConfig
  - npm scripts: start, package, make, publish, lint, test, test:watch, test:coverage


